          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1645550711835-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1645550711835-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1645550711835-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1645550711835-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved tomatoes</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> ground fennel seeds</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1645550723955-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1645550723955-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1645550723955-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1645550723955-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1645550723955-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir through the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1645550739203-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1645550739203-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1645550739203-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1645550739203-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1645550739203-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>linguine for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>linguine </strong>and return to the pot, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
